anyone with this error? do you know how to fix this?

Use at your own discretion, but here:

```sudo apt-get --purge -y remove '*cuda*' --allow-change-held-packages
sudo apt-get --purge -y remove '*nvidia*' --allow-change-held-packages
sudo apt autoremove -y
sudo apt purge
sudo apt clean```

Then find the right driver:
https://www.nvidia.com/Download/index.aspx?lang=en-us

then you need to make sure you have the cuda toolkit, test with
`python3 -c 'import torch; print(torch.cuda.is_available())'`

There is developer documentation at https://docs.bittensor.com/ which is an excellent start towards understanding the underlying network, and also information about installing the base Bittensor software (which you'll need to be able to use bittensor command line interface, or "btcli").

There are no one size fits all guides for mining/validating in general, though, because the network has been upgraded to support subnets, each of which can be competing to achieve different goals.  So your best bet is to just dig into the subnet channels if you want to understand them.

There's a community-run YouTube channel, the Bittensor Hub, which links to Bittensor-related videos (here: https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCungMFLM9PzEBMjJlAXQIHw ) but bear in mind that things change so quickly around here that many of them might already be out of date.

Lastly, there is a community-run Discord for third-party builders and people who are interested in approaching the token as an investment vehicle -- that server is here: https://discord.gg/j8TAzcpv8y -- if you're looking to check out the non-Foundation validators, for example, or you want to see what end-user-focuses products people are building using the Bittensor network, that's the place to be. : )

I should warn you that because Bittensor is getting some attention, it's also gotten the attention of scammers.  People reaching out to you via DM are most certainly scammers, especially if they're offering "support" or trying to get you to connect to some shady website (which they're using to steal your seed phrase), or outright asking you for your seed phrase.  In Discord it's possible to display a link but have the actual URL go elsewhere, so be very careful -- I'd recommend not accepting DMs at all.  Watch out also for people asking you to DM them -- sometimes we do need to invite people to do this, but you just need to be very sure that the person you're talking to is legitimate (and not, say, trying to spoof the "moderator" role by adding it to the "About Me" of their profile).

And you can also click on the name of a person who's posted in public chat and add your own personal note to their profile.  That way, if you want to double-check that someone in your DMs is the real deal, you can check their profile -- no note?  It's an imposter!

### 2024/01/27 - v1.3.0

I am thrilled to present the latest updates and improvements that we have implemented in our project over the past few days/weeks. 
Your ongoing commitment, dedication and patience have been crucial in achieving these advancements, and I want to extend my heartfelt congratulations and gratitude to each and every one of you.

Feel free to review the details in the PR and provide your feedback. Your experience is always valuable to us. Once again, congratulations to all for these collective achievements!

https://github.com/neuralinternet/compute-subnet/pull/106

Time estimated for the update to be live : EDIT: LIVE :Sui_Fire: 

No pressure, update at your earliest convenience please.
Bump of the set weights version will occur within the next weekend.

### Changelog:

### Validators/Miners
- Refactor axon PerfInfo into Specs.
  - @ Validators please run vali with `--validator.perform.hardware.query` if you intend using allocation.
- Logging, documentation, stability, and performance improvements.
- **Miners not running the last version of the code are now blacklisted by default by validators.**
### Validators
- DB improvements - Full history of the miners statistics until deregistration, from this update you'll be able to rerun without losing the global average score of the whole subnet.
- Optimization of the scoring system to consider the average of miners scoring and obtain much more stable and accurate data over time.
- Add `--validator.whitelist.updated.threshold` if you want to change the default value before using whitelist for miner updated. Default: 40.
### Miners
- Complete refactor of the class.
  - bugs squash: issue that stopped the main loop that could lead to not set_weights anymore and few logs.
- Add `--miner.whitelist.not.updated` Whitelist validators not using the last version of the code. Default: False.
- Add `--miner.whitelist.updated.threshold` if you want to change the default value before using whitelist for validator updated. Default: 40.

### Team still working on:
- remove docker requirement
- frontend
- compute subnet cli: enhance validator allocation
### Actions for this update:
```sh
git pull
python -m pip install -r requirements.txt
python -m pip install -e .
pm2 restart <id>
```
### Optional but recommended for validator:
```sh
rm database.db
```
Troubleshooting:
```sh
# If you meet any issue with the update, revert temporary the version:
git checkout 33431546f0d0f65702293ad0713a8e9cbbb4daad
```
Happy mining ⛏️  / validating 💂
